{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.23",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 23,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 23",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 23 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:2",
      "text": "Even to day is my complaint bitter: my stroke is heavier than my groaning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:3",
      "text": "Oh that I knew where I might find him! that I might come even to his seat!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:4",
      "text": "I would order my cause before him, and fill my mouth with arguments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:5",
      "text": "I would know the words which he would answer me, and understand what he would say unto me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:6",
      "text": "Will he plead against me with his great power? No; but he would put strength in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:7",
      "text": "There the righteous might dispute with him; so should I be delivered for ever from my judge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:8",
      "text": "Behold, I go forward, but he is not there; and backward, but I cannot perceive him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:9",
      "text": "On the left hand, where he doth work, but I cannot behold him: he hideth himself on the right hand, that I cannot see him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:10",
      "text": "But he knoweth the way that I take: when he hath tried me, I shall come forth as gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:11",
      "text": "My foot hath held his steps, his way have I kept, and not declined.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:12",
      "text": "Neither have I gone back from the commandment of his lips; I have esteemed the words of his mouth more than my necessary food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:13",
      "text": "But he is in one mind, and who can turn him? and what his soul desireth, even that he doeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:14",
      "text": "For he performeth the thing that is appointed for me: and many such things are with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:15",
      "text": "Therefore am I troubled at his presence: when I consider, I am afraid of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:16",
      "text": "For God maketh my heart soft, and the Almighty troubleth me:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.23.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 23:17",
      "text": "Because I was not cut off before the darkness, neither hath he covered the darkness from my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
